<paragraph id="84585F48FFF70148600EF72C91148937" blockId="21.[828,1437,1836,2051]" lastBlockId="22.[151,760,190,533]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B600EF72C90C98C61" bold="true" box="[828,952,1836,1859]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
The species was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6670F72C96E48C61" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1874" box="[1346,1429,1836,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6670F72C96E48C61" box="[1346,1429,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Aenidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was later synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B678AF74C96598C41" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1861" box="[1208,1320,1868,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Palpoxena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B678AF74C96598C41" box="[1208,1320,1868,1891]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Palpoxena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore recent authors classified 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6742F76C967B8CA1" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1884" box="[1136,1290,1900,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6742F76C967B8CA1" box="[1136,1290,1900,1923]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">A. sumatrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B661EF76C96ED8CA1" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1861" box="[1324,1436,1900,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Palpoxena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B661EF76C96ED8CA1" box="[1324,1436,1900,1923]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Palpoxena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6048F78C977D8C81" author="WILCOX J. A." box="[890,1036,1932,1955]" editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B672BF78C97D88C81" author="KIMOTO S." box="[1049,1193,1932,1955]" firstAuthor="KIMOTO" journalOrPublisher="Kurume University Journal" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="201 - 237" part="39" refId="ref31701" refString="KIMOTO S. 1990: Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2. Kurume University Journal 39: 201 - 237." title="Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2." type="journal article" year="1990">KIMOTO 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6785F78C96E98C81" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." box="[1207,1432,1932,1955]" firstAuthor="MOHAMEDSAID" journalOrPublisher="Wallaceana" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 5" part="74" refId="ref32623" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 1995 b: The biodiversity profile of the leaf beetle of the subfamily Galerucinae (Insecta: Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) from Danum Yalley, Sabah. Wallaceana 74: 1 - 5." title="The biodiversity profile of the leaf beetle of the subfamily Galerucinae (Insecta: Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) from Danum Yalley, Sabah" type="journal article" year="1995" yearSuffix="b">MOHAMEDSAID 1995b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B600EF7AC971B8CE1" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. &amp; FURTH D. G." box="[828,1130,1963,1987]" firstAuthor="MOHAMEDSAID" journalOrPublisher="International Scholarly Research Notices, Zoology" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 60" part="2011" refId="ref33093" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. &amp; FURTH D. G. 2011: Secondary sexual characteristics in the Galerucinae (sensu stricto) (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). International Scholarly Research Notices, Zoology 2011: 1 - 60." title="Secondary sexual characteristics in the Galerucinae (sensu stricto) (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="2011">MOHAMEDSAID &amp; FURTH 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The examination of the type specimens showed that males have a metasternal process and therefore 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B60ADF7EC97078321" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1884" box="[927,1142,2028,2051]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B60ADF7EC97078321" box="[927,1142,2028,2051]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Aenidea sumatrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6613F7EC96E78321" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[1313,1430,2028,2051]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6613F7EC96E78321" box="[1313,1430,2028,2051]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486387F0BE92E48BF7" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1899" box="[181,405,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ozomena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486387F0BE92E48BF7" box="[181,405,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Ozomena intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from an unknown number of specimens, presumably females as no male sexual characters were mentioned in the description (
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF401486199F0FE93A18A17" author="JACOBY M." firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin)" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" pagination="259 - 313" part="60" refId="ref31637" refString="JACOBY M. 1899: Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra. Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin) 60: 259 - 313 + 1 pl." title="Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1899">JACOBY 1899</bibRefCitation>
). The comparison of the specimens (both males and females) of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486228F13E92898A77" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1884" box="[282,504,318,341]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486228F13E92898A77" box="[282,504,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Aenidea sumatrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486102F13E93C88A57" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ozomena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486102F13E93C88A57" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Ozomena intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed no difference. The colouration of the female antennae is variable. In the darkest specimens (including the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF4014863F0F19E92678A97" box="[194,278,414,437]" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486272F19E91558A97" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1899" box="[320,548,414,437]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ozomena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486272F19E91558A97" box="[320,548,414,437]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Ozomena intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) the antennomeres VIII–X are yellow while all remaining antennomeres are contrastingly black. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486246F1DE91248AD7" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1899" box="[372,597,478,501]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ozomena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486246F1DE91248AD7" box="[372,597,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Ozomena intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed as a new synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF401486250F1FE912F8937" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[354,606,510,533]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF401486250F1FE912F8937" box="[354,606,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="45">Taumacera sumatrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
